  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, when determining the appropriate sentence, the court must weigh both aggravating and mitigating factors. The defendant has no prior criminal record and has already demonstrated a willingness to make amends by partially paying back the stolen funds. The outburst by the spectator demanding a 10-year sentence represents an emotional reaction, not an objective legal standard, and is entirely disregarded in this sentencing. Considering the defendant's lack of criminal history and proactive efforts towards restitution, a lengthy prison term is unnecessary. Nevertheless, a short period of incarceration is required to serve as a punitive measure for the breach of fiduciary duty and as a deterrent against future white-collar crimes.",
  "verdict": 6
